============
w3af webui
============

Intro
=====

This project provides web interface for w3af_ and is mostly built on:

* Django (https://www.djangoproject.com/).
* Celery (http://celeryproject.org/)

.. _w3af: http://w3af.org

Django
======

NB! w3af_webui requires at least 1.4 version of Django web framework :(
You can get it from https://www.djangoproject.com/download/

Install
=======

Install required dependences:

* w3af-console - In Debian based systems just install w3af-console or get fresh version from http://w3af.org
* MySQLdb - In Debian based systems just install python-mysqldb
* lxml - In Debian based systems just install python-lxml
* django - https://www.djangoproject.com/
* django_extensions - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install django-extensions
* south - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install south
* cronex - You can get it from https://github.com/jameseric/cronex
* ghettoq - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install ghettoq
* celery - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install celery
* djcelery - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install django-celery
* djkombu - You can install it from PyPI by easy_install django-kombu

Make database init: ::

    CREATE DATABASE w3af_webui CHARACTER SET utf8; 
    CREATE user w3af_webui@localhost IDENTIFIED BY "w3af_webui"; 
    GRANT ALL ON w3af_webui.* TO w3af_webui@localhost;
    FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

Dont forget to edit /etc/mysql/my.cnf: ::

    # [mysqld]
    # ...
    # transaction-isolation  = READ-COMMITTED

and restart mysql: ::

    /etc/init.d/mysql restart

To configure w3af_webui settings please edit file src/w3af_webui/settings.py.
Then create local_settings simlink: :: 

    cd src/w3af_webui
    ln -s local_settings.development.py local_settings.py

Create necessary directories: ::
    
    mkdir /var/local/w3af_webui
    chown USER:USER /var/local/w3af_webui
    mkdir /var/log/w3af-webui/
    chown USER:USER /var/log/w3af-webui

Database schema init: ::

    cd ../
    ./manage.py syncdb --noinput
    ./manage.py migrate

Run django via runserver: :: 
    
    ./manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8080

Run celery: ::

    ./manage celeryd -l INFO -B

Open in your browser http://0.0.0.0:8080/.
Default user is w3af_admin:w3af_admin

